description: A Bengaluru business development professional was terminated for threatening an influencer with acid attack over her clothing. The influencer's husband reported the incident to police and social media. Dehradun-based Etios Services fired Nikith Shetty and filed a case against him, emphasizing their commitment to women’s safety and zero tolerance for harassment.
title: Bengaluru man loses job after threatening acid attack over woman's clothes
PhD scholar orders rope online, hangs self at IIT-Kanpur hostel room

description: Two men arrested for the gang rape of a 17-year-old girl in Surat were trying to flee when caught. One suspect, Shivshankar Chaurasiya, died in custody after being moved to a hospital. He had a criminal history, including murder. Police are still searching for a third accomplice involved in the crime.
title: Surat gang rape accused dies hours after arrest

description: On Wednesday, Biden addressed the nation in a televised broadcast, warning of the potential devastation from Hurricane Milton, which had already begun to hit Florida’s coastline. During the press conference, a reporter asked whether DeSantis should have taken Harris’ calls. Rather than addressing the question directly, Biden praised DeSantis for his cooperation, saying he had found him to be "gracious" in their interactions and appreciated the acknowledgment of the federal response.
title: Why Biden called DeSantis ‘gracious’ after Florida Gov snubbed Harris
Ratan Tata flew his aircraft to Hubballi in 2013

description: In 2006, Ratan Tata collaborated with painter Lakshman Shrestha to create an artwork for a charity auction, dedicating several days to learning and painting. The artwork, valued at Rs 75 Lakh, now holds a prominent place in Mumbai’s Taj Mahal Palace lobby, contributing significantly to the funds raised.
title: Ratan Tata the artiste & his collaborative painting at Mumbai’s Taj Mahal Palace

description: Tata group of Airlines, which includes Air India, Air India Express, and Vistara, made in-flight announcements to honor Ratan Tata, who passed away at 86. CEO Campbell Wilson expressed condolences, recognizing Tata's significant contributions to Indian aviation. National leaders and state governments also paid their tributes.
title: Air India pays tribute to Ratan Tata with touching in-flight announcement

description: On the fourth day of the Multan Test, England posted their highest total in 86 years, declaring at 823 for 7 thanks to Harry Brook's triple century and Joe Root's double century. Pakistan's shocking batting collapse left them at 82 for 6, facing a likely defeat, despite a late unbeaten partnership from Agha Salman and Aamer Jamal. Pakistan were 152 for 6 at close of play on the penultimate day.
title: 'Cricket not safe in Pakistan': Fans roast hosts after collapse

description: Chum Darang from Arunachal Pradesh discusses her participation in Bigg Boss 18, highlighting her intent to showcase her home state, her concerns about losing privacy, and her refusal to tolerate disrespect. She emphasizes her preparedness to handle household chores and trolls, focusing on her own happiness while contending with judgment from viewers.
title: Bigg Boss 18's Chum Darang: I won't tolerate disrespect of any kind

description: Kate Middleton has ceased mediating between Prince William and Prince Harry. After completing preventive chemotherapy, she is now prioritizing her health and family. Tensions persist within the royal family, with minimal communication between Harry, Meghan, and the palace.
title: Has Kate given up on reuniting Prince William and Harry? What royal experts say

description: India's skipper Rohit Sharma might miss one of the first two Test matches in Australia due to personal reasons conveyed to the BCCI. Abhimanyu Easwaran is a probable replacement, with Shubman Gill and KL Rahul also as potential openers. Vice-captaincy plans remain undecided.
title: Rohit Sharma likely to miss one Test in Australia

description: Maharashtra's cabinet has requested an increase in the non-creamy layer income limit to Rs 15 lakh, granted constitutional status to the SC commission, and approved welfare corporations for journalists. Additional funds for the Balasaheb Thackeray Turmeric Research Centre and housing for various groups were also sanctioned. Other decisions include library culture promotion, childcare facilities, and an African safari in Nagpur.
title: From Hry playbook? Maha govt seeks hike in income cap for non-creamy layer

description: Law enforcement in west Delhi has confiscated 200 kg of cocaine worth Rs 2,000 crore, marking the second largest seizure within a week. This operation is suspected to be linked to a previous bust involving over 560 kg of cocaine and 40 kg of hydroponic marijuana, with six arrests made across multiple cities.
title: Delhi drug bust: Cops seize 200 kg of cocaine worth Rs 2K crore

description: BJP faced a tough defeat in Pir Panjal region, securing only one of eight assembly seats in Rajouri and Poonch, attributed to political dynamics post-abrogation of Article 370, polarisation over the Pahari quota row, and rising terrorist activities. National Conference and Congress dominated the remaining seats.
title: J&K assembly election: What pulled down BJP in Pir Panjal

description: Air India has firmed an order for 85 Airbus planes, including 75 A320s and 10 A350s. This follows Tata Group's massive 470-plane order worth $70 billion and includes an option to purchase more planes from Airbus and Boeing. Tata is also merging AirAsia India and Vistara into AI Express and AI, respectively.
title: Air India bumps up Airbus order by 85 aircraft

description: Dussehra, also known as Vijayadashami, is celebrated in India to mark the victory of Lord Ram over Ravana. The festival symbolizes the triumph of good over evil. It's celebrated with performances, fairs, and family gatherings. This year, Dussehra falls on October 12, 2024. Schools, colleges, and offices are closed for the celebration.
title: Happy Dussehra 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages, and quotes to share

description: Mercedes-Benz India warns that raising GST rates on electric vehicles above Rs 40 lakh could hinder investment, employment, and EV adoption. CEO Santosh Iyer argues that higher taxes on imported and locally-produced EVs would reduce demand and potentially neutralize government revenue gains from increased duties.
title: GST hike on electric vehicles to hit adoption: Mercedes-Benz

description: As the 2024 election looms, talks of leaving the US resurface among citizens, politicians, and public figures due to fears of a potential Trump return and his calls for retribution. Surveys indicate increased efforts to secure foreign visas, homes, and dual citizenship due to political uncertainty.
title: Trump triggers fresh talk of Americans' flight from USA

description: FMCG companies in India plan to hike prices of household essentials, including cooking oil, soaps, and detergents, due to rising commodity costs like palm oil and copra. This move adds upward pressure on inflation, with RBI closely monitoring the situation amidst geopolitical tensions and unexpected weather events affecting global prices.
title: Grocery bills to rise on commodity pain

description: Gurpatwant Singh Pannun of SFJ, designated as a terrorist by India, releases a video threatening to initiate independence movements in multiple Indian states and claims Arunachal Pradesh for China. He vows to use Canadian and American laws to destabilize India by 2047.

description: The Rock made a dramatic return in the final segment of 'Bad Blood', signaling intentions that hint at future storylines with Roman Reigns and Cody Rhodes. In an Instagram post, he teased further engagement, hinting at a potential electrifying feud ahead, keeping fans eagerly anticipating his next target, going forward.

description: During a Sheffield Shield match between New South Wales and South Australia, star bowler Nathan Lyon comically searched for a lost ball in the bushes. The ball had been hit over the fence, and Lyon initially found the wrong one. Lyon is preparing for the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy against India, revealing his strategy to tackle Rishabh Pant's aggressive batting.
title: Lyon's hilarious quest for lost ball in bushes. Watch

description: Rahul Gandhi's claim of a psychological advantage for the Congress after the Lok Sabha polls has been undermined by the Haryana election results. This outcome has shifted the pressure onto the opposition, highlighting the necessity of alliances, as shown by the Congress's missed opportunity with AAP. The upcoming Maharashtra elections now pose a significant challenge.

description: In 2008, Ratan Tata shifted his Rs 1,500 crore Nano project from West Bengal to Gujarat due to protests led by Mamata Banerjee after the state government refused to return 400 acres of farmland. Narendra Modi, then Gujarat's Chief Minister, welcomed Tata, ensuring the project stayed in India. Production of Nano cars ceased in 2018.
title: How an SMS from then-CM Modi brought Nano to Gujarat

description: The Indian government officially bans Hizb-ut-Tahrir, a pan-Islamic organisation founded in 1953, for allegedly promoting terrorism and radicalising youth to join groups like ISIS. The group is accused of using social media and secure apps for terrorist activities and aims to establish a global Islamic caliphate by overthrowing democratic governments.
title: Centre bans Hizb-ut-Tahrir, labels it a threat to national security

description: Donald Trump, in a recent podcast, claimed that foreign entities, possibly Iran, might have been involved in two attempted assassinations on him in 2024. He criticized the FBI for not unlocking the attackers' encrypted phones and stressed the need for national security measures, hinting at foreign involvement in political violence.
title: Trump on who tried to get him assassinated: 'I think it was ... '

description: The digital world pays tribute to Ratan Tata, who passed away at 86. Websites of Tata Group companies such as TCS, Croma, and Tata Steel have turned their homepages into solemn memorials. The homages reflect on his impactful leadership and compassionate approach, offering links to obituaries and remembrance articles on his life.
title: TCS, Croma, Tata Steel and other Tata websites change homepage to pay homage to Ratan Tata
How Ziklag plans to turn US into 'biblical America' under Trump

description: The 90s music videos served as launchpads for stars like Malaika Arora and Shahid Kapoor, capturing India's cultural pulse. Iconic tracks like 'Aankhon Mein' and 'Yaad Piya Ki Aane Lagi' featured memorable performances, blending romance and innocence. These classics continue to influence today's music-video aesthetics, showcasing timeless charm and creativity.
title: Sameera Reddy, Riya Sen, Shahid Kapoor: Trendsetting stars of 90s music videos

description: Ratan Tata's purchase of Jaguar and Land Rover in 2008 signified a striking turnaround from being disparaged by Ford officials a decade earlier. Ford, on the verge of bankruptcy, viewed the $2.3 billion deal as salvation. Additionally, Tata unveiled the affordable Nano car, emphasizing his vision of providing reliable transportation for Indian families.
title: How Ford's insult led Ratan Tata to buy Jaguar, Land Rover

description: Taylor Swift's influence on Travis Kelce has led to him trying new foods, improving his culinary horizons. His brother, Jason Kelce, noted this positive change on their podcast. Swift's presence has also been a supportive factor during Kelce's football season.
title: Jason Kelce is thankful to Taylor Swift for changing Travis Kelce's food habits

description: In a grand celebration of Amitabh Bachchan's 82nd birthday on Kaun Banega Crorepati, Aamir Khan and son Junaid join him. Aamir and Bachchan share thoughtful advice for aspiring actors, emphasizing the significance of cultural immersion in India for authentic performances.

description: Ratan Naval Tata, chairman emeritus of Tata Group, passed away at 86. A respected figure in Indian industry, Tata was admired for his patriotism, knowledge, and courtesy. TCS competitor and Infosys co-founder NR Narayana Murthy expressed deep respect for Tata, recalling their collaboration honoring Jamshedji Tata in 2004.
title: When Ratan Tata asked Narayana Murthy why he invited one of Infosys' 'biggest competitor'

description: South Korean author Han Kang wins the Nobel Prize in Literature 2024 for her intense poetic prose confronting historical traumas. The Nobel committee announces this alongside other 2024 laureates, including awards in Medicine, Physics, and Chemistry recognizing groundbreaking contributions in their fields.
title: Nobel prize 2024: South Korean poet Han Kang gets literature award

description: Harry Brook and Joe Root set a record-breaking 454-run partnership in the fourth day of the first Test against Pakistan in Multan, leading England to a total of 823 runs for seven wickets declared. This remarkable achievement includes Root becoming England's highest Test run-scorer and Brook scoring a stunning 317.

description: The Karnataka government is forming a Special Investigation Team (SIT) and a cabinet subcommittee to address the alleged Covid scam during the previous BJP government. An interim report recommends recovering Rs 500 crores, highlighting significant financial mismanagement of Covid-19 relief funds.
title: Karnataka Cabinet orders SIT investigation amid Covid scam allegations under previous BJP government

description: The National Conference in Jammu and Kashmir has garnered support from four Independents, bringing its total to 46 seats. Omar Abdullah has been chosen as the leader and is in discussions with the Congress for support. Emphasis is on passing a resolution to restore the region's statehood.

description: Ratan Tata, former chairman of Tata Group, showed remarkable leadership during the 26/11 Mumbai terror attacks. At the age of 70, he ensured the safety and support of victims and their families, and later established a trust to provide humanitarian aid during disasters.
title: When Tata stood outside Taj Hotel for 3 days during 26/11 attack

description: Ola's AI chatbot, Krutrim, has criticised CEO Bhavish Aggarwal's dismissive response towards comedian Kunal Kamra's complaint about Ola's EV service backlog. Krutrim suggested a more professional and empathetic approach to addressing customer concerns.

description: SP chief Akhilesh Yadav confirmed the alliance with the Congress amid ticket distributions for the upcoming UP assembly bypolls. Despite the Congress' demands for more seats, the SP announced candidates for six key constituencies. The INDIA bloc alliance remains intact, though any future seat-sharing agreements will be decided by Yadav. The actual bypolls will test the coalition's strength.

description: Joe Root's double century against Pakistan at the Multan Cricket Stadium highlights his skill and calm under pressure. Despite an early drop by Babar Azam, Root capitalized and completed his double ton off 305 balls with 14 boundaries, reinforcing his status among cricket's elite.

description: Union home minister Amit Shah expressed condolences over the death of Ratan Tata, highlighting his transformative leadership of the Tata Group and contribution to various fields. Tata, a global industry icon, passed away at 86. A state funeral will be held in Mumbai.
title: 'Tata's legacy will continue to guide future business leaders': Amit Shah

description: Bombay House, the Tata Group’s headquarters, uniquely welcomes stray dogs due to Ratan Tata’s compassion. His empathy led to creating a dedicated kennel within the building and special care for strays. Ratan Tata's concern for animals also extended to the Taj Hotel and the establishment of a pet hospital in Mumbai. He passed away at 86.

description: Sumit Antil, a two-time world champion, set a new Paralympic record at the Paris Paralympics by throwing 70.59m, defending his F64 javelin title. Known for his mental strength and rigorous training, Antil plans to refine his technique further. Despite injury challenges, he remains dedicated and envisions greater achievements in future competitions.
title: 'Comparison with Neeraj Chopra is silly': Sumit Antil

description: Harry Brook from England scores his first triple century at the age of 25 in the opening Test against Pakistan. He and Joe Root set a record-breaking 454-run partnership, the highest ever for England in Test cricket. Brook's historic performance included 28 fours and three sixes, and marks England's first triple century since 1990.

description: The BBC apologizes for a technical error in its weather app that incorrectly forecasted extreme weather conditions, including hurricane-force winds and temperatures of 404°C. The Met Office provides accurate updates, noting the UK's expected weather and ruling out the current possibility of hurricane impacts.
title: BBC apologises after weather app gaffe shows 'hurricane winds' in London

description: Former cricketer Jatin Paranjpe backs India to win the Border-Gavaskar Trophy for the third consecutive series in Australia. With Rohit Sharma leading, Paranjpe predicts a 3-2 or 4-1 victory. He discusses key players, including Shami, Siraj, and potential third openers like Gill and Shaw, as well as the handling of rising star Mayank Yadav.

description: Ratan Tata, a known animal lover, prioritized his ailing dog over receiving a prestigious award from Prince Charles in 2018. At Tata Group’s Bombay House headquarters, stray dogs are welcomed and even have a dedicated kennel.

description: Amazon India is under scrutiny after a user revealed Chirag Gupta's frequent wins in their contests, sparking allegations of bias. Over the last decade, Gupta has won six separate contests, prompting widespread speculation and criticism from other users about potential insider favoritism.

description: Union minister Piyush Goyal reminisces about Late Ratan Tata, highlighting his thoughtfulness, philanthropy, and humble nature. Tata's contributions during the Covid-19 pandemic and support for public health initiatives like the Dr Hedgewar Hospital are acknowledged, emphasizing the legacy he leaves behind. The veteran industrialist was remembered fondly by many as his body was taken for its final journey.

description: With IPL franchises finalising their retentions for the 2025 mega auction, all eyes are on Mumbai Indians and Rohit Sharma's fate. Harbhajan Singh believes Rohit Sharma could trigger a bidding war if not retained. Separately, Harbhajan Singh emphasized India's safety concerns about traveling to Pakistan for the ICC Champions Trophy.

description: Mukesh Ambani and his family paid their last respects to Ratan Tata in Mumbai, following Tata's demise. Tata had served as the chairman of the Tata Group and played a pivotal role in leading the conglomerate to unparalleled achievements.
title: Watch: Mukesh Ambani and Nita Ambani pay last respects to Ratan Tata

description: Two poultry farm owners in Bahraich, Uttar Pradesh, allegedly thrashed and humiliated three Dalit boys, accusing them of stealing wheat. The boys faced physical abuse and public shaming. A police case has been filed against the accused under multiple charges. The victims' families claim the boys were punished for not reporting to work, not for theft.

description: Ratan Tata, the chairman emeritus of Tata Sons, has passed away at 86, leaving the nation mourning. Known for his industrial and philanthropic impact, he also amassed millions of followers on social media.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi attended the Phalak-Phralam performance in Laos and participated in a Buddhist blessing ceremony, emphasizing the shared cultural heritage between India and Laos. The visit also highlighted restoration efforts at Vat Phou temple and aimed to deepen cooperation during Asean-India and East Asia summits.

description: AAP shared images of Delhi chief minister Atishi signing files at home, after alleging she was forcibly vacated from her bungalow. AAP leader Sanjay Singh criticized BJP for the eviction during Navratri. Both political parties are engaged in a blame game over the chief minister’s official residence, with differing claims on whether proper procedures were followed.

description: Rafael Nadal, Spain’s tennis icon and 22-time Grand Slam singles champion, announced his retirement at the end of the season following the Davis Cup final. In a heartfelt message, the 38-year-old reflected on his recent struggles. Renowned for his dominance at the French Open with 14 titles, Nadal’s departure signals the end of an era in tennis.

description: Shantanu Naidu, long-time associate of Ratan Tata, bid farewell to Tata, leading the hearse carrying Tata's remains on a motorcycle. Naidu, who started the 'Motopaws' venture, was personally invited by Tata in 2014 to join the Tata group. He later pursued an MBA at Cornell and returned to work for Tata Trusts as promised.

description: Ratan Tata's passing on October 9 prompted notable tributes, including one from Punjabi superstar Diljit Dosanjh, who paused his Germany concert to honor the revered industrialist. Diljit praised Tata's lifelong dedication and philanthropy. Actor Raghav labeled Tata a 'national gem,' emphasizing his wisdom on heart over wealth. Celebrities, including Salman Khan and Boney Kapoor, expressed their sorrow, highlighting Tata's legacy as a visionary and inspiring philanthropist. Tata's death marks a significant loss, with many mourning his exceptional contributions to India.

description: Delhi BJP president Virendra Sachdeva accuses AAP of stalling the handover of the CM's residence to hide corruption. AAP counters, alleging BJP influence in the eviction. PWD confirms possession and ongoing inventory work, with discussions about legal obligations and protocols for residence allocation.

description: Despite this, TCS will announce its performance post-board meeting.

description: Joe Root showcased remarkable composure, scoring his sixth double century in Test cricket, surpassing legends like Rahul Dravid, Alastair Cook, and Graeme Smith. Root's sixth double-century achievement joins an elite roster with names such as Sachin Tendulkar, Ricky Ponting, and Virender Sehwag. description: Hurricane Milton's powerful winds severely damaged Tropicana Field's roof as the storm battered Florida's Gulf Coast. The stadium, used as a staging area for storm relief efforts, saw no injuries reported. Significant flooding and widespread power outages impacted the region, causing unprecedented infrastructure damage in St. Petersburg.

description: Ratan Tata, chairman emeritus of Tata Sons, passed away at 86. Known for revolutionizing India's automotive industry, Tata's legacy includes the launch of the Tata Indica, the development of the Tata Nano, and the acquisition of Jaguar Land Rover. His vision and bold moves transformed Tata Motors and left an enduring impact on global automotive history.
title: Remembering Ratan Tata and cars close to his heart beyond the Nano

description: Over 100 workers from Telangana have arrived in Tel Aviv to work in construction, despite Israel's ongoing war with its neighbors. description: Zomato CEO Deepinder Goyal highlighted issues faced by delivery executives in malls by sharing a video of his experience. The post garnered attention, leading BJP Yuva Morcha Chief Tejasvi Surya to outline measures taken in Bengaluru South, such as setting up resting points with essential amenities for delivery partners.
title: Why Zomato CEO Deepinder Goyal thanked BJP's Tejasvi Surya

description: Noel Tata, 67, emerges as a leading candidate for the role of chairman at Tata Trusts following Ratan Tata's passing. He hold significant positions across several Tata Group companies and is a trustee of Sir Ratan Tata and Sir Dorabji Tata Trusts.
title: Who is Noel Tata? Possible successor at Tata Trusts

description: WWF’s Living Planet Report highlights India's food consumption pattern as the most sustainable among G20 countries. It mentions that adopting India's pattern worldwide would need less than one Earth by 2050. India’s millet mission and climate-resilient millets are praised. The report stresses promoting healthy alternative protein sources to reduce land needed for food production.
title: The way Indians eat is best for Earth: WWF Living Planet Report

description: Simi Garewal had once admitted that she was dating Ratan Tata for a brief period of time. She later married someone else, but they continued to remain close friends. Tata breathed his last at Breach Candy hospital on Wednesday, due to prolonged illness. He will be accorded a state funeral and Maharashtra has declared a day or mourning today.

description: India secured a dominant 86-run victory against Bangladesh in the second T20I, driven by Rinku Singh's 53 and Nitish Kumar Reddy's 74. Their 108-run partnership resurrected India's innings from 41/3 to a total of 221/9, bolstered by aggressive guidance from head coach Gautam Gambhir and captain Suryakumar Yadav.

description: Mayank Yadav's selection for India's T20I series against Bangladesh garners attention due to his impressive IPL 2024 performance, consistently bowling over 150kmph. Despite an abdominal strain, he recovered at NCA Bengaluru. His debut against Bangladesh included a maiden over and his first international wicket, yet he hasn't crossed 150kmph in international play.

description: Rinku Singh's partnership with Nitish Kumar Reddy helped India secure an 86-run win over Bangladesh in the second T20I, clinching the series 2-0. Despite early challenges, their 108-run stand set a competitive total. Singh praised coach Gautam Gambhir's influence and expressed his ambition to represent India in all formats.

description: Grazer wins the Fat Bear Contest with over 40,000 votes, beating Chunk, who killed her cub this summer. The Katmai National Park event highlights bears’ winter preparation. Grazer's strength and distinct appearance contribute to her victory, while Chunk's size and aggressiveness make him a fierce competitor.

description: A 35-year-old woman from London, who claimed she was kidnapped by a cabbie in Hyderabad, was found in Goa after abandoning her children. Police discovered she was with the driver voluntarily. After being tracked down, she confessed and was sent back to London, while the cabbie was warned and released.

description: The AAP has condemned the BJP for allegedly forcing the vacating of the CM house at 6, Flagstaff Road, leading to the removal of CM Atishi's belongings. The party accuses the BJP of having an anti-women mindset, while LG office sources claim the residence is not officially allotted to Atishi.

description: Ratan Tata, the respected industrialist and philanthropist, passed away at 86 on Wednesday. As a former chairman of Tata Sons, he played a crucial role in India's economy and supported Indian cricket by offering job opportunities and financial aid to players, greatly impacting their careers.
title: Cricket legends who were employed by Ratan Tata

description: A hacker claims to have released sensitive data of 3.1 crore Star Health customers on Telegram. The data includes personal details, insurance claims, and more. Star Health confirmed a cyberattack and stated that investigations are ongoing.

description: During the second T20I match between India and Bangladesh, Riyan Parag's delivery was declared a no-ball as his back foot landed outside the pitch tramlines while attempting an unconventional bowling style. India secured an 86-run victory, leading the series 2-0 ahead of the final T20I in Hyderabad. The third and final T20I will be played on Saturday at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium in Hyderabad.

description: Shantanu Naidu, Ratan Tata's trusted assistant, mourned the death of the visionary leader, who passed away at 86 after a brief illness. Their bond began in 2014 over a shared love for animals. In a post on LinkedIn, Shantanu shared his grief, sharing a photo with Ratan Tata, his 'dear lighthouse' expressing the deep void left by the industrialist's passing.

description: Ratan Tata, with millions of followers on X and Instagram, emerged as an unexpected social media star. Known for his nostalgic posts, messages of empathy, and personal reflections, Tata’s social media presence has evolved into a platform for support amidst false claims and widespread admiration.

description: Ratan Tata's strategic acquisitions, starting with Tetley in 2000 for $432 million, transformed Tata Group into a global powerhouse. He orchestrated over 60 acquisitions, including Jaguar-Land Rover. While successes mounted, not all ventures thrived, such as Tata Steel's Corus purchase. description: Following Ratan Tata's passing, Tata Trusts faces a crucial decision in selecting a new chairman. With Noel Tata emerging as the likely candidate, his appointment would uphold the tradition of having a Parsi leader and maintain a connection to the founding family.

description: Ratan Tata guided the Tata Group into new sectors like telecom and cars, and drove innovation with projects like the Indica and Nano. He oversaw over 60 acquisitions and took TCS public. After appointing and later replacing Cyrus Mistry, his philanthropic efforts through Tata Trusts transformed healthcare and education. Post-retirement, he invested in startups like Upstox and Ola Electric.

description: Ratan Tata's legacy lives on through his impactful yet humble leadership. Known for his integrity and commitment, he turned challenges into triumphs, exemplified by his role in launching the Nano car and uniting the Tata Group during tumultuous times. His grace and dedication leave a lasting mark on India's business landscape.

description: On 10.10.24, individuals are influenced by their numerology numbers, affecting their personal and professional interactions. From taking bold actions, focusing on relationships, to seeking introspection, each number guides on how to navigate the day's specific energies and challenges while emphasizing communication, patience, and self-reflection.

description: The 2025 Met Gala theme "Superfine: Tailoring Black Style" celebrates Black dandyism's historical and cultural influence on fashion from the 18th century to today. He expressed respect for the students who sacrificed their lives and explained his brief political role, while also appealing for support as he heads towards Test retirement
title: Shakib Al Hasan apologises for 'silence' during Bangladesh protests

The film, an investigative thriller, sees Rajinikanth shine in the first half, but the second half draws mixed reviews. Notable performances include Fahadh Faasil, Amitabh Bachchan, and Manju Warrier.
title: 'Vettaiyan' X review: Rajinikanth shines in this investigative thriller

description: Anand Mahindra paid tribute to Ratan Tata, lauding his significant contributions to India's economic advancement and expressing sorrow over his passing. Tata Sons chairman N Chandrasekaran also expressed profound loss, highlighting Tata's impact on the Tata Group and India. Ratan Tata passed away at the age of 86.
title: Anand Mahindra pays tribute to Ratan Tata: ‘I am unable to accept…’

description: Two days after CM Atishi moved her belongings to the former residence of Arvind Kejriwal, PWD took possession of the property, sparking controversy. The CMO alleged forced eviction by LG among BJP's influence. BJP sought a probe over procedural violations, while AAP defended the actions, claiming it follows standard protocols for CM residences.
title: Delhi CM Atishi & LG’s fight reaches ‘her’ house, her belongings removed

description: Ratan Tata, Chairman Emeritus of Tata Sons, passed away in Mumbai, marking the end of a remarkable corporate journey. A few years ago, Narayna Murthy presented the Life Time Achievement Award to Ratan Tata and touched his feet while doing so.
title: When Narayana Murthy touched Ratan Tata’s feet

description: The Puri-New Delhi Purushottam Express was delayed for over three hours in Uttar Pradesh due to a false security alert about suspected terrorists with explosives. Passengers were subjected to thorough security checks from 2:30 am to 6:00 am, but no threats were found. Despite the disruption, authorities ensured all safety protocols were followed.
title: Train halts for over 3 hours in UP amid bomb scare

description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde announced that late industrialist Ratan Tata, who passed away at 86, will be given a state funeral. Shinde highlighted Tata's unique blend of morality and entrepreneurship, calling him a living legend. Tata's remains will be kept at the NCPA in Mumbai for public homage. His resilience during the 26/11 terror attacks was also noted.
title: Maharashtra govt announces state funeral for Ratan Tata

description: Ratan Tata strategically used retirement policies to consolidate power and modernize Tata Group starting in 1992. He mandated directors retire at 75, forcing several senior leaders out. The policy evolved over the years, reflecting his evolving strategy and maintaining his influence.
title: How Ratan Tata unseated old guard to gain control, reshape the group

description: Ratan Tata, post-retirement, invested in over 50 startups including Snapdeal, Ola, and Paytm, using personal investment vehicle RNT Associates and UC-RNT, aiding their growth with his significant insights. Many startups benefitted from his mentorship, with some going public and delivering multi-bagger returns.
title: Startups looked up to him as mentor, not just as investor

description: The Tata Nano, conceptualized by Ratan Tata to offer an affordable car for middle-class Indians, faced numerous challenges. Despite initial popularity, issues from factory location controversies, safety concerns, and its branding as a 'poor man's car' led to its decline and eventual discontinuation by 2019.
title: Ratan Tata's most audacious project: Nano's 'cheap' tag proved costly

description: Ratan Tata's leadership during India's economic liberalisation transformed Tata Group through strategic divestments, global partnerships, and key acquisitions like Jaguar-Land Rover. He improved corporate governance, solidified control, and took TCS public, raising $1.2 billion. Despite crises, including a financial scandal and terrorist attack, Tata’s legacy endures, leaving a monumental impact on Indian business.
title: Visionary who led Tatas' revenue from $4bn to $100bn

description: On October 10th, the 10:10 portal is believed to open, offering a potent time for manifestation and transformation. Spiritual communities worldwide engage in meditations and rituals to harness this cosmic energy, setting clear intentions to align their desires with universal forces.
title: What can you manifest through the cosmic energy of 10:10 portal?

description: Ratan Naval Tata passed away at 86. He led the Tata Group's transformation into a global giant, significantly boosting revenue and diversifying its portfolio. Known for innovation and philanthropy, his tenure saw projects like Nano and acquisitions expanding Tata's reach. Post-retirement, he remained active in startups and charity.
title: India loses a Ratan: The visionary who took India Inc global passes away at 86

description: Congress finds itself in a tough spot in Uttar Pradesh after Samajwadi Party, its INDIA bloc ally, announced candidates for six out of 10 bypoll seats without consultation. This move disrupts Congress's plans to contest five seats in alliance with SP.
title: UP bypolls: Samajwadi Party announces candidates, takes Congress by surprise

description: Ratan Tata, with millions of followers on X and Instagram, emerged as an unexpected social media star. Known for his nostalgic posts, messages of empathy, and personal reflections, Tata’s social media presence has evolved into a platform for support amidst false claims and widespread admiration.
title: An unlikely Insta sensation who beat many an influencer

description: Ratan Tata's strategic acquisitions, starting with Tetley in 2000 for $432 million, transformed Tata Group into a global powerhouse. He orchestrated over 60 acquisitions, including Jaguar-Land Rover. While successes mounted, not all ventures thrived, such as Tata Steel's Corus purchase. The journey redefined India's corporate footprint internationally.
title: The dealmaker who took India global with a slew of big buys

description: Following Ratan Tata's passing, Tata Trusts faces a crucial decision in selecting a new chairman. With Noel Tata emerging as the likely candidate, his appointment would uphold the tradition of having a Parsi leader and maintain a connection to the founding family.
title: Ratan Tata passes away: Trusts must pick successor from among trustees

description: Ratan Tata guided the Tata Group into new sectors like telecom and cars, and drove innovation with projects like the Indica and Nano. He oversaw over 60 acquisitions and took TCS public. After appointing and later replacing Cyrus Mistry, his philanthropic efforts through Tata Trusts transformed healthcare and education. Post-retirement, he invested in startups like Upstox and Ola Electric.
title: Ratan Tata chose to stay out of limelight

description: Ratan Tata's legacy lives on through his impactful yet humble leadership. Known for his integrity and commitment, he turned challenges into triumphs, exemplified by his role in launching the Nano car and uniting the Tata Group during tumultuous times. His grace and dedication leave a lasting mark on India's business landscape.
title: Ratan Tata: A legacy has moved on, leaving behind his legacy

description: Nitish Kumar Reddy smashed seven sixes and four boundaries for 74 runs off 34 balls during the second T20I against Bangladesh at the Arun Jaitley Stadium in New Delhi. The eventual 86-run win gave India an unbeatable 2-0 lead in the series.
title: IND vs BAN: Nitish smacks seven sixes as hosts shatter records

description: Hackers have exploited a zero-day security flaw in Qualcomm chipsets used in many popular Android devices, as confirmed by Google and Amnesty International. Qualcomm stated that fixes have been issued to manufacturers, who now need to roll out updates to users. Millions of devices, including those from Motorola, OnePlus, Oppo, and Xiaomi, could be affected.
title: Qualcomm has a’ hacking warning' for OnePlus, & other Android users

description: A special PMLA court in Bengaluru has acknowledged the ED's chargesheet against former Karnataka minister B Nagendra for allegedly masterminding a ₹20 crore scam involving ST welfare funds, intended for use in the 2024 Lok Sabha elections. The investigation revealed substantial misappropriation and money laundering.
title: K’taka ex-mantri kingpin of Valmiki corp scam: ED

description: The CISO of Star Health Insurance is accused by a hacker named xenZen of being behind a massive customer data breach via API access. UK-based researcher Jason Parker confirmed the authenticity of the hacker's claims. Star Health is investigating and has sought an injunction to prevent data access.
title: Star Health CISO leaked customer data, says hacker

description: The Akhil Bharatiya Akhara Parishad has urged Hindus to buy from shops with visible signs of Sanatan Dharma adherence, due to alleged contamination of food and worship items by individuals of a specific religion. ABAP highlights these issues in preparation for Maha Kumbh in Prayagraj.
title: Buy only from Sanatanis, says Akhara Parishad

description: The absence of a Congress-AAP alliance in the Haryana assembly elections likely did not cost Congress the victory. Only in three of the 53 contested seats did AAP's votes exceed the winning margins, potentially adding just three more seats to Congress's tally.
title: AAP alliance could've helped Cong in Hry, but just to boost its tally by 3

description: The recent govt survey reveals average out-of-pocket medical expenses for hospitalisation in rural and urban areas at Rs 4,129 and Rs 5,290, respectively. Non-hospitalisation costs are Rs 539 and Rs 606. Literacy and numeracy rates are high in the 15-24 age group, while 23.3% are not in education, employment, or training. Most households have a telephone or mobile connection.
title: Govt study: Rural households' spend on hosp stay Rs 4,129/yr, urban Rs 5,290

description: After Congress rejected the Haryana election results as 'unexpected and unacceptable,' party leaders met with the Election Commission (EC) demanding a thorough investigation. The EC criticized Congress spokespersons Jairam Ramesh and Pawan Khera for allegedly undermining democratic principles while acknowledging complaints about EVM issues.
title: Congress seeks probe; Election Commission states, party rejecting will of people

description: Omar Abdullah, vice president of National Conference, declared that the new government would immediately pass a resolution for restoring J&K's statehood, urging the Prime Minister to act on this promise. He also acknowledged Article 370's complexities, urging future engagement. Coalition discussions with PDP are not prioritized. His son Zamir criticized Center's alleged strategies to undermine NC.
title: Statehood resolution to be passed in 1st cabinet meet: Omar Abdullah

description: Ministry of Heavy Industries has asked ARAI to provide details on alleged consumer rights violations by Ola Electric, a beneficiary of government EV incentive schemes. The move follows a notice from CCPA citing over 10,600 complaints, including misleading ads, unfair trade practices, and service delays.
title: List 'consumer rights violations' by Ola Electric: Govt to ARAI

description: The National Conference-Congress alliance won the Kashmir region, seen as a rejection of the BJP's policies post-2019. The BJP's strategy to use proxies in Kashmir failed, leading to a significant setback. While the BJP maintained a hold in Jammu, the results indicate dissatisfaction with changes in Kashmir's status.
title: Naya Kashmir? BJP's Jammu confinement reeks of the old

description: BJP's dominance in SC-reserved seats in Jammu and Haryana signals erosion of Congress's influence and casts doubt on allegations against Modi government's stance on caste quotas. BJP benefitted from inclusive development focus and addressing Dalit concerns beyond major castes, contrasting Congress's perceived biases.
title: BJP's pro-Dalit policies beat Congress quota narrative: Experts

description: The National Conference sources indicated that reversing the 10% ST reservation for the Pahari community in Jammu and Kashmir is unlikely, fearing agitations. They argue that changes might spark protests, affecting the new government. BJP's failure to win in Pahari-populated areas further complicates the situation.
title: NC unlikely to reverse 10% ST quota for Paharis in J&K

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 10, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today, October 10, 2024: Read your astrological predictions
